#27949

```
vscode.workspace.onDidCloseTextDocument((textDocument: vscode.TextDocument) => {
    console.log("closed => " + textDocument.isClosed)
}, null, context.subscriptions);
```

This is fired twice each time a document is closed, once where `textDocument.fileName` is `<path>`, once where it's `<path>.git`. Is that expected?

Repros with extensions disabled.

I had the following:

```ts
			const linkHandler = new TestTerminalLinkHandler(new TestXterm(), Platform.Windows, null, null,
				new TestContextService(new TestWorkspace('C:\\base')));
```

I added a new param to the constructor so I pasted in `, null` to the end, and it went and tried to guess the indentation. It should only ever do this when it inserts new lines imo.

```ts
			const linkHandler = new TestTerminalLinkHandler(new TestXterm(), Platform.Windows, null, null,
			new TestContextService(new TestWorkspace('C:\\base')), null);
```

Testing #28465

I have `syntaxProfiles.json` like

```
{
    "html": {
        "tag_case": "upper"
    }
}
```

when I change it to `"lower"`, the change doesn't take effect until I restart vscode.
